  <section class="ps5-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="ps5-container">
      <div class="ps5-section-header">
        <h2 class="ps5-section-title">PS5 Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="ps5-section-subtitle">Common questions about PS5 repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ps5-faq-list">
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix PS5 overheating in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — we fully disassemble the PS5, deep clean all cooling channels, and apply high-performance thermal paste to the APU and VRAM. Most overheating repairs are completed same-day when dropped off before noon at our Winnipeg St. Vital location.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair DualSense controller stick drift in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — we repair analog stick drift on both standard DualSense and DualSense Edge controllers, typically within 1–2 hours at our Winnipeg location. We also repair adaptive trigger failures, unresponsive touchpads, broken bumpers, and USB-C charging port damage.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix PS5 HDMI port issues in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — HDMI port repair is one of our most common PS5 repairs and our technicians perform precision board-level micro-soldering under magnification. We repair broken HDMI connectors, lifted solder pads, and motherboard trace damage that most general repair shops in Winnipeg cannot handle.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you upgrade PS5 storage in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — we install larger NVMe M.2 PCIe 4.0 SSDs in PS5 consoles up to 4TB capacity. We'll recommend the right drive for your budget, install it correctly, and ensure the required heatsink is properly fitted as per Sony's official installation guidance.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix PS5 disc drive problems?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — we diagnose and repair PS5 disc reading issues, stuck discs, ejecting problems, and drive mechanism failures. We also discuss disc drive upgrade options for PS5 Digital Edition owners — contact us to confirm availability before visiting.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>How much does PS5 HDMI repair cost in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">PS5 HDMI repair costs depend on the extent of the damage — a straightforward port replacement costs less than a repair involving lifted motherboard pads and trace damage. We provide a clear diagnostic and upfront quote before starting any work so you know exactly what you're paying for.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Is PS5 HDMI repair done the same day in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Many PS5 HDMI repairs are completed same-day when dropped off at our Winnipeg St. Vital location before noon. Cases involving significant motherboard trace damage may require additional time — we'll give you an accurate estimate after the initial diagnostic.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Why does my PS5 keep overheating and shutting down?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">PS5 overheating is almost always caused by dust buildup clogging the heatsink fins and degraded thermal compound on the APU pushing temperatures past safe limits. A full disassembly, deep clean, and thermal paste replacement typically resolves the issue completely — and is one of the best value repairs you can do on a PS5 to extend its lifespan.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you offer a warranty on PS5 repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — we offer a lifetime warranty on most PS5 HDMI port and DualSense controller repairs. Overheating repairs include a 90-day warranty. If the same issue returns within the warranty period, we repair it at no charge.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ps5-faq-item">
          <summary class="ps5-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair PS5 consoles in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ps5-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ps5-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts PS5 repairs Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. Calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability and give you an accurate turnaround estimate before your visit.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

